article_metadata.title: Photo gallery: Statues for artificial reef crushed after barge flips | Sun., June 7, 2015 | Miami Herald

og.description: A barge carrying massive Easter Island-inspired sculptures flipped over Sunday, crushing the statues and sending them into the water upside-down. The project was intended to create an artificial reef off the coast of Deerfield Beach.
